		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message31756001">Taking a stab at this from a different approach, it's important to keep in mind that because there is a lower budget on these works, it also means the producers care less about the product. This allows for more artistic freedom in and of itself. This particular contribution has nothing to do with the effect of constraints but the confounding relationship between budget and freedom.<br />
<br />
While I don't think this contributes to all of the creativity birthed from limited budgets, I think it has made a nonnegligible effect.</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><div style="text-align: center;"><!--link--><a href="http://myanimelist.net/clubs.php?cid=40791">QD</a><!--center--></div></div></td>
