		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message31846305">While I do agree with what nil is saying, I believe that in the wrong hands a low budget can really impact the show negatively enough to make the freedom almost pointless. Wake Up Girls is the fitting example of this, where it's very spotty use of budget for big moments was not enough to make up for the truly poor looking sections of the show. On the other end of the spectrum, I feel like No Game No Life is doing an excellent job of adding flourishes when necessary while also keeping the look as seemingly consistent as possible. <br />
<br />
Also it would be a crime to have a topic like this and not mention The Tatami Galaxy. Masterful use of live action film and simple animation set to well written characters are just some of the characteristics that make it a favorite of mine.</div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
